    {
      "id": "7771fe5e-db00-4a1b-8788-d3776d54d734",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        4300,
        200
      ],
      "name": "Build final sub-workflow response",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const data = $input.first().json;\n\nconst isEscalation = data.escalate === true && !data.validated_response;\n\nreturn [{ json: {\n  status: 'success',\n  result: {\n    validated_response: data.validated_response || '',\n    next_stage: data.next_stage || '',\n    action: data.action || 'none',\n    cta_triggered: data.cta_triggered ?? false,\n    escalate: data.escalate ?? false,\n    escalation_reason: data.escalation_reason || null,\n    validation_passed: data.validation_passed ?? false,\n    rewrite_applied: data.rewrite_applied ?? false\n  },\n  error: null\n} }];"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "c96a44b6-608e-483f-a98e-e94fe2cafac5",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        4600,
        200
      ],
      "name": "Sticky note — Validation logic",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## WA_05 — Validate and Filter Response\n\n**Purpose:** Enforce strict quality rules on the candidate response before it reaches the user.\n\n**Validation checks:**\n1. Word count ≤ 80\n2. Single question only (max 1 `?`)\n3. Forward motion present (CTA/question signal)\n4. No guardrail violations (forbidden phrases)\n5. No generic AI language\n\n**On failure:**\n- Retry up to 2 times via Claude rewrite\n- If still failing after 2 retries → escalate signal\n\n**Output contract:** `{ status, result, error }`",
        "height": 300,
        "width": 340
      }
    }
